cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.SY 

This paper is primarily focused on neural networks and their implementation on hardware devices such as memristors and flash memory cells. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses low-rank approximations and streaming methods, which are relevant to the fields of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), and cs.EM (Electromagnetics). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm and architecture for implementing the SBE approach, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
